1.1 Data preparation

I’ll be using a kaggle dataset for day one’s task of plotting points on a map. Data can be obtained here.

We only need coordinate pairs here, so we’ll go ahead and extract them from the data. We’ll also remove any duplicates as they won’t add anything to a simple points plot.

nyc_points <- nyc_airbnb %>% 
  select(c(latitude, longitude)) %>% 
  distinct()

summary(nyc_points)
##     latitude       longitude     
##  Min.   :40.50   Min.   :-74.24  
##  1st Qu.:40.69   1st Qu.:-73.98  
##  Median :40.72   Median :-73.96  
##  Mean   :40.73   Mean   :-73.95  
##  3rd Qu.:40.76   3rd Qu.:-73.94  
##  Max.   :40.91   Max.   :-73.71

All the values here look reasonable so we’ll go ahead and make our plot.

1.2 Plot

qmplot(longitude, latitude, data = nyc_points, 
       geom = "blank", zoom = 10, maptype = "toner-lite", 
       darken = .2, legend = "topleft") +
  geom_point(data = nyc_points, aes(x = longitude, y = latitude), 
             size=0.3, alpha=0.2) +
  coord_sf() +
  theme_classic()
